<font color="#FF0000">WHIRLY BIRDS, THE MOVIE</font><br>
<tt>Fri Aug 29 14:42:06 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Gun run, get your silly whirly blades outta here. <br>
I got the commies corners and here you come in with your whirly blades, Always, always, just when we got them there gooks cornered and we have them just where we wanted them, u airheads always showed up and scared them away. <br>
Could never have any fun. Just when we would fix bayonets and got the taste of blood in our mouths your swift moving, easy gliding, dust polluting, noise making machines would show up, shoot up the place and split.<br>
 <br>
We would ask for a chow run and none of you guys would be around, but when we said we had them cornered.<br>
 oH! then you weren't too busy then, were you? <br>
Though it was fun, used to lined up, one chopper behind the other but you still missed. You guys never could find the target, I can't recall how many times we had to crawl out there tie a smoking grenade to a gook so that you could find them. I mean what a game that was pull the pin on the grenade and place it on charlie's chest, then wait and see if you could find it. And you know what we heard?<br><br>
Oh! Ahh!, Roger, on that, AHH! AHH! what color smoke is that again?<br><br>
And then, you guys never, never thanked us for holding the target still while you practiced new gun and rocket technics. <br><br>
Oh! and I'm sorry about ripping off one of your Mickey Mouse helmets, didn't know it had to be plugged in for the radio to work, worthless piece of trash, ever try to cook in it?<br>
It had a little radio attached to it. Didn't work, kept pushing all the buttons and it just kept beeping and beeping. No music, no Hanoi Hanna, no sound, just a whole bunch a worthless beeping. <br><br>
I think it was some type of remote control cause one night we took it out with us on an ambush and this crazy chopper followed us. We would push a button and this crazy chopper would turn right, pushed another and the chopper turned left. Played with it all night long. Finally we  tied it to a water bufflo and I'll be darn if that chopper didn't follow that poor water bufflo all of the next day. Poor water buffolo gave him the runs, guess he was scared being followed by a green noisy machine all day long.<br><br>
Brought the helmet home still use it on Holloween. But no one ever told me what's so special about it. Has writing on it. Special This and Special Force that. But it's just a green plastic helmet belonged to some US Army Major, wonder if he missed it?
<p><code>--    :)  (Sparrowhawk) </code><p>


